OL,3,CWoman jailed after trafficking drugs
OL,4,Cdisguised as bath salts through airport
OL,6,FShe was initially sentenced to nine
OL,7,Fyears in prison, reduced to seven
OL,8,Fyears and six months with credit
OL,9,Ffollowing a guilty plea.
OL,11,FDuring Kavanagh's sentencing, Judge
OL,12,FWilliams said: "You knew you were
OL,13,Fplaying for high stakes, and you lost."
OL,15,FDetective Constable Rhys Richards, of
OL,16,FTarian, said Kavanagh was a "pivotal
OL,17,Fmember" of an organised crime group
OL,18,Fwho was tasked with receiving Class A
OL,19,Fdrugs "with a potential street value
OL,20,Fof hundreds of thousands of pounds."
